column5: So your pain is of being a lesbian? Why do you hate it so much?

That they view me differently, and that i might not be able to change that, they wont view me as me but as someone that needs help, someone thats depressed, and maybe my parents might think they failed me, even though its not their fault, i dont want to give them that thought.
By the lake, in a small log cabin, stone fire, cosy as fuck, sofa, blankets, carpet, my girlfriend, cuddling. Fuck, i want that now
Im.. 16, i cant yo to a therapist without telling my parents, which right now is what im figuring out
Maybe in time, but right now, i have got no clue, i know i should get help, tell someone about how i feel, but i genuinely dont know how
Hmmm, wonder why that is... oh wait
Dude, call your mum and talk to her for a bit, even if its just to say hi, or that you live her, there may be no coming back fton this for you, but if you love her, let her know.
Yeah i get you, im just scared or people seeing me differently
Hey, thanks man, im trying to build up to taking to someone eventually, so its not completely out of the picture, but  i just feel like i could get some relief out of iy
